Analysis of Data Availability

Library Imports

library(readxl)
library(ggplot2)
library(knitr)
library(dplyr)

source('themes/theme_main.R')

Problem

This document generates insights about the volatile compound and sample availability of the GC-MS data.

Definitions

1. TotalVolatileUbiquityBySample: This is the number of compounds that are present for a given sample.

2. TotalVolatileAbundanceBySample: The total cumulative sum of all the volatile concentrations for a given sample

3. TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatile: The total number of samples that the given volatile is expressed in

Data Loading & Curation

# loading the GCMS phenotype table
gcms_pheno_tbl <- read_excel('data/processed/sup_tbl_1-final_gcms_phenotype_table_v2.xlsx')
dim(gcms_pheno_tbl)
[1] 515 107
# create a GCMS phenotype table without apple id
gcms_pheno_tbl.noaid <- gcms_pheno_tbl[, 2:ncol(gcms_pheno_tbl)]
dim(gcms_pheno_tbl.noaid)
[1] 515 106
# load the volatile classification data
classification_dat <- read_excel('data/processed/final_compounds_table_rev2_addressed.xlsx')
classification_dat <- classification_dat[, c("Name", "Classification")]
dim(classification_dat)
[1] 106   2

Figures

Figure 1 Volatile Composition across all apple accessions

Figure 1A: Distribution of total abundance & ubiquity

We first need to calculate the total sample ubiquity by volatiles.

TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles <- colSums(gcms_pheno_tbl.noaid != 0)
TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles.df <- data.frame(
        Name = names(TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles),
        TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles = TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles
)
TotalAbundanceByVolatile <- colSums(gcms_pheno_tbl.noaid)

Distribution of Sample Ubiquity for Volatiles

total_sample_ubiquity_by_volatiles_plot <- ggplot(
  TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles.df,
  aes(x = reorder(Name, -TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles), y = TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles)
) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_avenir(
    panel_x = F,
    panel_y = F,
    grid = F,
    axis = T,
    axis_col = "black",
    ticks = T
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10, hjust = 0.5, vjust = -0.5),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 13, hjust = 0.5, margin = margin(t = 10, r = 0, b = 0, l = 0)),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 13, hjust = 0.5, margin = margin(t = 0, r = 10, b = 0, l = 0)),
  ) +
  ylab("Number of Samples") +
  xlab("") +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0))
ggsave(
  'figures/data-availability/total_sample_ubiquity_by_volatiles_plot.png',
  total_sample_ubiquity_by_volatiles_plot,
  height = 15
)

Distribution of Sample Ubiquity by Volatile Classes

TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatileClass.df <-
  inner_join(TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles.df, classification_dat, by = "Name")

How many compounds are in each class?

TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatileClass.df <- TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatileClass.df %>%
  group_by(Classification) %>%
  dplyr::do(data.frame(
    .,
    Compounds = length(.$Classification),
    UltimateUbiquity = sum(.$TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles)
  ))
total_sample_ubiquity_by_volatile_classes_plot <- ggplot(
  TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatileClass.df,
  aes(y = TotalSampleUbiquityByVolatiles, x = reorder(Classification, UltimateUbiquity)
  )) +
  geom_bar(
    position = position_stack(reverse = TRUE),
    stat = "identity",
    color = "black"
  ) +
  coord_flip() +
  xlab("") +
  ylab("Total Ubiquity") +
  GLOBAL_THEME +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0)) +
  theme(
    axis.text.y = element_text(hjust = 1, vjust = 0),
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank()
  )
ggsave(
  'figures/data-availability/total_sample_ubiquity_by_volatile_classes_plot.png',
  total_sample_ubiquity_by_volatile_classes_plot
)
